BEGIN_TEXT
Let 
\(A\) be a \( a \times b \) matrix.  If the linear transformation 
\(T(x)\) from \({\mathbb R}^$m\) to  \({\mathbb R}^$n\) is defined by
\(T(x) = Ax\), how many rows and columns does the matrix \(A\) have?


$BR
\( a= \) \{ans_rule(10) \},  
\( b= \) \{ans_rule(10) \}


END_TEXT

